  <sect1 id="&app;-intro">
    <title>Introduction</title>

    <figure id="&app;-fig">
      <title>&appname; Applet</title>
      <screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject><imagedata
            fileref="figures/&app;.png" format="PNG"/>
          </imageobject>
          <textobject>
            <phrase>The &appname; applet.</phrase>
          </textobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </screenshot>
    </figure>

    <para> The &appnameapp; applet lets you browse and open files in your computer directly from the panel.</para>
    <para> The &appnameapp; applet is not intended as replacement to proper file managers like nautilus. Sometimes you just want to open a file and don't want to have to open a file manager, browse to and open the file, then close the file manager. This applet just saves you couple of clicks.</para>

	<sect2 id="&app;-intro-add">
      <title>Adding &appname; to a Panel</title>
	  <para> To add &appname; to a panel, right-click on the panel, then choose <guimenu>Add to Panel...</guimenu>, select <guimenu>&appnameinpanel;</guimenu> from the list and press <guimenu>OK</guimenu>.</para>

    <figure id="running-fig">
